* Description

  This repository is for CM9 on HTC golfu.
  It is still a work in progress.


* How To Build CM9 for HTC golfu

  Make a workspace

  $ cd ~
  $ mkdir android
  $ cd android
  $ mkdir system
  $ cd system


  Do repo init & sync

  $ repo init -u git://github.com/CyanogenMod/android.git -b ics
  $ repo sync -j16



  Clone Golfu CM9 source code

  $ cd device
  $ mkdir htc
  $ cd htc
  $ git clone git://github.com/munjeni/android_device_htc_golfu.git golfu



  Make vendor specific files

  Connect your device runing stockrom to the your local machine and execute script!

  $ cd golfu
  $ ./extract-files.sh
  $ cd ../../..



  Copy msm7627a audio source code to the android/hardware/qcom

  $ cd android/hardware/qcom && git clone git://github.com/cm2pico/android_hardware_qcom_audio.git audio
  $ cd ../../..



  Setup vendor

  $ cd vendor/cm/
  $ ./get-prebuilts

  Setup environment

  $ source build/envsetup.sh
  $ lunch cm_golfu-userdebug


  Build CM9

  $ make otapackage -j4


* Thanks

